Denote $x = \frac{\tan(\alpha + B)}{\tan \alpha} = \frac{\tan \alpha \cos \beta + \tan \beta \cos \alpha}{\tan \alpha \sin \beta - \tan\beta \cos \alpha}$, or equivalently, $\tan(\alpha + \beta) = x\tan \alpha - \tan \beta$. Then notice that $\sin 3\alpha = 3 \tan \alpha - \tan^3\alpha$, while \begin{align*} \cos3\alpha \sin \beta & = \frac{1}{3}\Big[(\beta + \alpha)\Big]\alpha\beta\tan(\alpha + \beta) - \vec\beta\tan^3\alpha + \beta\tan\alpha - 2(\beta + \alpha)\tan\alpha\Big]\\[0.1cm] & = \frac{x - x^3}{2}\tan\alpha - \tan\beta + \tan^2 \alpha. \end{align*}

