[asy]
Label f;

f.p=fontsize(6);

xaxis(0,3,Ticks(f, 1.0));

yaxis(0,5,Ticks(f, 1.0));

fill((0,1)--(0,4)--(2,0)--(1,0)--cycle, grey);
draw((-.5,5)--(2.5,-1), dashed, Arrows);
draw((-1,2)--(2,-1), dashed, Arrows);
[/asy]

The upper diagonal line is the graph of $2x+y=4$. The lower diagonal line is the graph of $x+y=1$. The y-axis is the graph of $x=0$ and the x-axis is the graph of $y=0$. The shaded region includes the solutions to the system. The longest side is the upper diagonal side. The length of this side is $\sqrt{4^2+2^2}=2\sqrt{5}.$ Thus $a+b=2+5=\boxed{7}$.

